<h1 class="text-h2 md:text-h1 text-gray-1000 mb-0px">Investing in Growth Stocks</h1>
<div class="font-medium text-gray-800 text-md md:text-lg mb-16px mt-20px md:my-24px">
By
<a class="text-cyan-800 hover:text-cyan-600 hover:underline" href="https://www.fool.com/author/2330/">Adam Levy</a> 
Updated
May 3, 2023 at 5:24PM
</div>
</div>
<div class="border-gray-200 -mx-24px md:-mx-40px h-1px border-b-1px md:border-b-0px pt-16px md:pt-0px md:h-16px md:bg-gradient-to-b from-transparent to-gray-200"></div>
</section>
<section class="container mx-auto bg-white px-24px md:px-40 pt-16px md:pb-8">
<div class="mx-auto md:max-w-880 lg:max-w-1280">
<div class="mt-20px md:mt-36px
          foolcom-grid-content-sidebar">
<div class="max-w-full mx-auto tailwind-article-body">
<section class="block-paragraph">
<p data-block-key="g1sin">Investing in growth stocks can be a great way to earn life-changing wealth in the stock market. The key, of course, is to know which growth stocks to buy -- and when.</p><p data-block-key="d1ktv">Many growth stocks have been routed through the first half of 2022. While the <a href="https://www.fool.com/investing/stock-market/indexes/sp-500/"><b>S&amp;P 500 index</b></a> crashed about 20%, the S&amp;P 500 Growth index fell 28% through the first six months of 2022. Some growth stocks fell much more, with stock prices cut by half or two-thirds. If you can identify a growth stock with strong fundamentals, now could be a great opportunity to invest.</p><p data-block-key="cfbrg">To help you get started, heres a handy guide to growth investing. With these tools and strategies, youll be able to position your portfolio for long-term success with growth stocks.</p>
</section>
<section class="block-brightcove_video_embed">
<div style="max-width: 960px; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
<style>video-js.video-js.vjs-fluid:not(.vjs-audio-only-mode) {padding-top: 56.25%;}</style>
<video-js data-account="6275808953001" data-player="1LZNDpg2B" data-embed="default" controls="" data-video-id="6301609229001" class="vjs-fluid"></video-js>
</div>
